# Misar.Dev Rules for Cursor

## MCP Servers (install: bash scripts/install.sh)
Add to Cursor Settings → MCP → Add Server:
- misarcoder: python3 ~/.claude/scripts/misarcoder-mcp.py
- guardrails:  python3 ~/.claude/scripts/guardrails-mcp.py  (env: ASSISTERS_API_KEY)
- guardian:    python3 ~/.claude/scripts/guardian-mcp.py    (env: SEMGREP_BIN=semgrep)

## AI API
Never use OpenAI/Anthropic/Google SDKs directly.
Use: baseURL=https://assisters.dev/api/v1, model=assisters-chat-v1, key=$ASSISTERS_API_KEY

## Code Standards
- TypeScript strict — no `as any`
- Supabase: `.maybeSingle()` not `.single()`; add types to database.ts
- Zod validate all POST route inputs
- No speculative abstractions — only what the task requires
- Conventional commits: `<type>(<scope>): <description>`
- Never commit secrets — use .env (gitignored)
- CSRF protection on all state-mutating endpoints
- WCAG 2.1 AA — 4.5:1 text contrast, 44px touch targets

## Infrastructure (Misar AI)
- Forgejo git.misar.io (not GitHub)
- Coolify hosting (not Vercel/Netlify)
- Self-hosted Supabase per product
- MisarMail for email (not SendGrid/Resend)
- Redis misar-redis container (not Upstash)

## Available Audits (ask the AI to run these)
security · full-suite · qa · uiux · seo · compliance · software-engineer
brand · marketing · billing · tester · content · product · auditor
